            <entry xml:id="entry_arǧonaq" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d3010e66" xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>arǧonaq</orth></form>
                <form xml:id="form_d3010e69" xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>arǧunaq</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d3010e72"><sense xml:id="sense_d3010e73"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>породистая собака</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>pedigree dog</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d3010e82"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>борзая</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>greyhound</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3010e94">
                        <quote>mæ arǧonaq kʼæbyla dæm ærbarvītʒynæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>я пришлю тебе моего борзого щенка</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I will send you my greyhound puppy</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>11</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e116" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>arǧamaq, arǧəmaq</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e121" xml:lang="ug"><lang/>
                        <w>arǧun</w>
                        <gloss><q>аргамак</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e129" xml:lang="ug"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>породистая лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>I 299, 301, 302</biblScope></bibl>).
                    Перенос значения с лошади на собаку следует объяснять тем, что уже на тюркской
                    почве слово получило атрибутивное употребление: %iarǧamaq at%i ‘породистая
                    лошадь’; ср. также русское употребление слова %iборзой%i как эпитета одинаково и
                    собаки и лошади. Передвижению значения способствовало то, что в аргамаке и в
                    борзой ценится одно и то же качество: резвость. Ср. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e139" xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>tāzī</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">1.</note>
                        <gloss><q>арабская лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e150" xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">2.</note>
                        <gloss><q>борзая собака</q></gloss></mentioned>. Осетинская форма
                    базируется, по-видимому, на несохранившейся (?) тюрк. %i*arǧunaq%i,
                    промежуточной между <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e158" xml:lang="ug"><lang/>
                        <w>arǧun</w></mentioned> и совр. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e163" xml:lang="tr"><lang/>
                        <w>arǧəmaq</w></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Cf. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e176" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>arǧamaq, arǧəmaq</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e181" xml:lang="ug"><lang/>
                        <w>arǧun</w>
                        <gloss><q>argamak</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e189" xml:lang="ug"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>thoroughbred horse</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>I 299, 301, 302</biblScope></bibl>).
                    The semantic shift from horses to dogs should be accounted for by the fact that
                    the word have already received an attributive use on Turkic ground: %iarǧamaq
                    at%i ‘thoroughbred horse’; cf. also the Russian use of the word %iборзой%i as an
                    epithet both for dogs and horses. The semantic shift was facilitated by the fact
                    that the same quality, namely agility, is appreciated in argamaks and in
                    greyhounds. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e199" xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>tāzī</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">1.</note>
                        <gloss><q>Arabian horse</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e210" xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">2.</note>
                        <gloss><q>борзая собака</q></gloss></mentioned>. The Ossetic from is
                    probably based on a non-preserved (?) Turkic %i*arǧunaq%i, intermediate for
                        <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e218" xml:lang="ug"><lang/>
                        <w>arǧun</w></mentioned> and modern <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3010e223" xml:lang="tr"><lang/>
                        <w>arǧəmaq</w></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
